‚Äî Nelson Mandela

Our new series of posts celebrates Challenge Charter Middle School #BLM Art with quotes about race. Help us celebrate our scholars as they share their creative expression on such an important matter. Check back each weekday for a new one here and on IG (@challengecharter).

‚ÄúOne either allows racial inequities to persevere, as a racist, or confronts racial inequities, as an antiracist. There is no in-between safe space of ‚Äúnot racist.‚Äù The claim of ‚Äúnot racist‚Äù neutrality is a mask for racism.‚Äù
‚Äï Ibram X. Kendi

Notice: Looking for a computer or tablet for learning at home? The following student populations are eligible for devices:

Charter school students living in temporary housing and in foster care are eligible to receive a device. This includes students living in shelter, as well as students living with another family or other person because of loss of housing or as a result of economic hardship. To request a device, please fill out the survey with the required information.

Families that want to request a device should fill out this survey. Share this information and the following URL with your school community: https://coronavirus.schools.nyc/RemoteLearningDevices.

This and other updates are on our Family Resource page. https://challengecharterschools.org/family-resources

post_text:
Great news! The New York City Department of Education is committed to making three free meals available daily for any New Yorker. Any New Yorker who wants one can get three free meals a day at more than 400 Meal Hubs across the city.

Meals can be picked up at all Meal Hubs 7:30 am to 1:30 pm, Monday through Friday

Meals Hubs will operate for children and families from 7:30 am to 11:30 am, and for adults from 11:30 am to 1:30 pm

No one will be turned away at any time

All adults and children can pick up three meals at one time

Vegetarian and halal options available at all sites

No dining space is available, so meals must be eaten off premises

Parents and guardians may pick up meals for their children

No registration or ID required

Destiny Williams of Class 501 loves to cook and sing, and she knows she's Challenge strong.

"At Challenge I've learned to never give up and to always give it your best. They make people feel welcome here, and the staff treats us fairly. Challenge feels like home."

Interested in applying? Don't wait! The deadline to apply for our 2020-21 school year is April 1st at 5:00P. We are accepting K-10 grade students and we accept transferring students. Our Career and Technical Education High School offers industry certification or associates degree. Apply at www.challengecharterschools.org.

#IamChallengeStrong #CheetahPride #ShareThisPost

"I‚Äôm Challenge Strong because of Challenge Charter School‚Äôs outstanding academics and the unique way they do things. CCMS really prepares students for their state exams.
